Program: The Why Factor
Title: Why Does Everyone Wear Trainers?
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p035q112
Last Broadcast Date: Mon 26 Oct 2015
Sneaker, trainer call them what you will. How did this product of the industrial revolution and a rising middle class become a global fashion item worth tens of billions of dollars a year? Especially when 85% of the purchases are never intended for its original purpose, health and fitness. Join Mike Williams for the Why Factor on Sneakers. Produced by Julie Ball (Photo: A man looks at a collection of sneakers in the window of a shopping mall, in the outskirts of Sao Paulo, Brazil. Credit: Getty Images) Show less